Paper: hep-th/9405192

Date: 1994-05-31

Title: Structure of Lorentzian algebras and Conformal Field Theory

Authors: V. Marotta and A. Sciarrino

Comments: 37 pages and 4 figures (not enclosed), Latex, DSF-T-93/44

The main properties of indefinite Kac-Moody and Borcherds algebras,considered in a unified way as Lorentzian algebras, are reviewed. Theconnection with the conformal field theory of the vertex operator constructionis discussed. By the folding procedure a class of subalgebras is obtained.